commit f59338db5fd29ea8f69fdd0a36257349c0ea9970
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 10:18:56 2026 -0400

    feat(cms)(list-edit): applyListEdit id-keyed add/remove/reorder + control-field parser
    
    ListEdit is the one deep operation realizing ADR 0006: applyListEdit(base, ops)
    navigates to each target list by dotted path and applies an id-keyed add /
    remove / reorder against the encoded document — identity, not array position, is
    the key. An id absent is appended, present-but-unnamed survives, reorder is an
    explicit permutation that never drops an item. Pure: clones once, never mutates.
    
    Private sugar around that capability: addOp/removeOp/reorderOp constructors,
    collectListOps (parses the list:<path>:<kind> control fields the admin view will
    submit, kept out of assembleOverrides' dotted-path namespace), and fieldName /
    listOpFieldName id-keyed templates that replace the positional ones the index
    merge relied on.
    
    Tests pin add/remove/reorder round-trips, id-keyed deep-field preservation,
    nested list-path navigation, input immutability, ordered application, and — via
    defaultContent — that removing a speaker still decodes while an added empty item
    is publish-invalid (strict decode rejects it, ADR 0006 consequence).
    
    The deepMerge index-branch / positional-template deletions land in 2.4 (migrate
    callers first).

